	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				 If you are itching to bash magic only critters, put a lightstone (any type) in your off hand. You are now able to bash magic. Simple, cheap and easy. <BR>
 To answer the question on how you sell a LORE item will take an explanation. There are two types of limitations on item posession and trade: LORE and NO DROP. If an item is LORE, you may only possess one at a time, period (they fixed the bank, try it before you flame). If an item is NO DROP, then you may not trade it to another player or sell it to a vendor once it has entered your inventory. Some (most) NO DROP items are quest related and may be given to a particular NPC to complete that quest, and NO DROP items can still be destroyed. An item may be both LORE and NO DROP or just have one limitation. This shield is just LORE, so the person who tried to loot a second one recieved a message like &quot;You already have one of this lore item&quot; and the second one remained on the corpse. If an item is just NO DROP, you can have as many as you like, but you may not trade or sell them (You can give them to ANY NPC, but if it is not the correct one the item will just disappear). Hope that helps.
				</font>
			</td>

